msg: On the fs-successor-ids branch, fix a typo in r1167533.
With this change, the basic unit test (r1167661) passes if I comment out the
first of its two "Validate" blocks; namely, it succeeds in walking the
successors chain one link forwards, but it fails to deliver on the API
promise of also reporting the node-rev itself as an interesting location,
were it interesting (in this case, because it was added).
(svn_fs_bdb__successors_add): Add a debug print, similar to the one FSFS has now.
